\cf3 On these 2009 per-person figures, China only ranked 65th. This is a dot plot of average energy use per person, again with the top 25 countries identified. Some of the countries at the top are the same. Others are different. So our new question is, "How well does energy use predict CO2 emissions?" Energy use and CO2 emissions are both numeric variables. And the standard tool for looking at a relationship between two numeric variables is a scatter plot. Here we have a scatter plot of per-person CO2 emissions against energy use for the country's heading our CO2 emissions list. This plot has a scale for CO2 emissions running vertically and a scale for energy use running horizontally.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
