\cf3 We plot each pair of points (same row) against these two scales as shown in the plot using the values for Kuwait in red and the United Arab Emirates in blue. We use the vertical axis for an outcome variable and the horizontal axis for a predictor variable. Most people will be familiar with this basic form of plot construction. If you're not, pause the movie and look carefully at how the information for these two countries has been placed on the graph.\
