\cf3 Discounting outlying Iceland, the pattern is strong enough that if we knew a country's per-person energy use, we would have a reasonable idea of its likely CO2 emissions as we've done here. While most scatter plots can be usefully viewed in terms of trend and scatter with the occasional outlier, there are exceptions such as in the following plots. This is data on petal widths and petal lengths of iris flowers. It is from a famous data set called Fisher's Iris Data. The most striking feature is the clear separation into two clusters. Clustering points to the existence of distinctly different groups and should set us wondering about what the defining characteristics for those groups might be.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
